						               													<description>CHATTERBOX - The Good News - Bad News Game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This simple game comprises two decks of cards - Good News and Bad News - which are shuffled together to form a pack.  Players sit in a circle, with one being elected to start.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The starter draws the top card from the deck and reads it aloud and throws the &amp;quot;Chat Bag&amp;quot; (bean bag) to one of the other players who must then come up with a response to statement read.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;e.g.&amp;#10;The Good News is .... the Mother-in-law is coming to dinner&amp;#10;The Bad News is ....&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The responder then takes the next card reads it aloud and throws the &amp;quot;Chat Bag&amp;quot; to another player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play continues like this until a player is eliminated under one of the following circumstances:&amp;#10;- The order of Good News - Bad News is forgotten&amp;#10;- A player hesitates for too long before giving a response&amp;#10;- The same response is given more than once.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is won by the last player left in the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
